                                                    <comments>
                    <comment id="12568968" author="jukkaz" created="Thu, 14 Feb 2008 15:33:06 +0000"  >Do we have a list of features/improvements in Lucene 2.3 that would benefit Jackrabbit?</comment>
                    <comment id="12570188" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 19 Feb 2008 12:14:14 +0000"  >- There is now a background segment merging feature available in Lucene. Our own merging might be obsolete now.&lt;br/&gt;
- There are a couple of performance improvements that we could benefit from.</comment>
                    <comment id="12570189" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 19 Feb 2008 12:14:37 +0000"  >See: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/lucene/java/tags/lucene_2_3_0/CHANGES.txt&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/lucene/java/tags/lucene_2_3_0/CHANGES.txt&lt;/a&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12577506" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2008 16:41:12 +0000"  >The following issue blocks us from upgrading to 2.3: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1221&quot; title=&quot;DocumentsWriter truncates term text at \uFFFF&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;LUCENE-1221&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12626040" author="sridhar.raman" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2008 10:19:26 +0100"  >Is there atleast a patch that would be provided if someone _needs_ to use Jackrabbit 1.4 and Lucene 2.3 in the same app?</comment>
                    <comment id="12626082" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2008 12:33:31 +0100"  >No, there isn&amp;#39;t.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Migrating to lucene 2.3 involves significant changes to the jackrabbit internal index readers, which extend from lucene. In addition, a migration process must be written because of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1221&quot; title=&quot;DocumentsWriter truncates term text at \uFFFF&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;LUCENE-1221&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.</comment>
                    <comment id="12630779" author="fgiust" created="Sat, 13 Sep 2008 16:02:04 +0100"  >&amp;gt;  In addition, a migration process must be written because of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1221&quot; title=&quot;DocumentsWriter truncates term text at \uFFFF&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;LUCENE-1221&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
does this involves only the lucene index, or the \uFFFF separator is contained somewhere in the repository?&lt;br/&gt;
If it&amp;#39;s only in the index, couldn&amp;#39;t be safe to just upgrate to the lucene 2.3 API and forse users to regenerate the lucene index when upgrading? (given that also the lucene index format is changed from 2.2 to 2.3 and, although compatible, recreating it from scratch wouldn&amp;#39;t hurt)&lt;br/&gt;
The long list of performace improvements in lucene 2.3 could really worth the upgrade...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12630958" author="mreutegg" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2008 09:28:41 +0100"  >&amp;gt; does this involves only the lucene index, or the \uFFFF separator is contained somewhere in the repository?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
it&amp;#39;s only in the index.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; [...] and forse users to regenerate the lucene index when upgrading?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
that&amp;#39;s an option, but I prefer an automatic migration whenever possible.</comment>
                    <comment id="12631813" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 17 Sep 2008 16:39:19 +0100"  >This patch contains the required changes that allow Jackrabbit to work with Lucene 2.3.x.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Feedback welcome.</comment>
                    <comment id="12632204" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 18 Sep 2008 14:18:31 +0100"  >Committed patch in revision: 696653</comment>
